BIG O NOTATION

Big O notation represents the performance of an algorithm as the size of input increases.

Types of Complexity

Time Complexity
Time taken by an algorithm to run.

Space Complexity
Memory required by an algorithm.


Common Time Complexities

O(1) → Constant
O(n) → Linear
O(log n) → Logarithmic
O(n²) → Quadratic
O(2ⁿ) → Exponential


Complexity Rules

Single instruction → O(1)

Example
a = 10


Single loop → O(n)

for i in range(n):
    print(i)


Nested loop → O(n²)

for i in range(n):
    for j in range(n):
        print(i,j)


Reducing input by half → O(log n)

n = 64
while n > 1:
    n = n // 2
    print(n)
